==English==

===Etymology===
Anglicization of Acadian French ''Acadien'' - Acadian, reflecting the palatization of (dj) in the Acadian dialect.

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪdʒən|-eɪdʒən]]

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun|s}}
#A member of an [[ethnic]] group of [[Acadian]] [[French]] origin, primarily living in Southern [[Louisiana]].

===Proper adjective===
'''Cajun'''
#Relating to the Cajun people or their culture or food

===Alternative spellings===
*Cajin, Cadjin, Cagin (obsolete), Cadien (French orthography)

